SIMPLE: tomorrow
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tomorrow
<hw>To*mor"row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Prep. <ets>to +
morrow</ets>.]</ety> <def>On the day after the present day; on the next
day; on the morrow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Summon him <qex>to-morrow</qex> to the Tower.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tomorrow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tomorrow
<hw>To*mor"row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The day after the
present; the morrow.</def>⟦ldquo⟧<xex>To-morrow</xex> is our wedding
day.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au> Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One today is worth two <qex>to-morrows</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Franklin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tompion</ent>⟦br⟧
